texts.text: TU7 was a version of Xbox 360 Edition released on December 19, 2012.[1] This version is based on Java Edition 1.0.0.

1 Additions
1.1 General
1.2 Gameplay
1.3 Blocks
1.4 Items
1.5 World generation
1.6 Mobs
2 Changes
2.1 General
2.2 Blocks and items
2.3 Mobs
3 References

1.4.6 Feature: Item name appears above hotbar when switching to it.
Phases of the moon added
New tutorial world with new biome
New mini-tutorials for new features
Updated new music disc quest
How to play: new section to brewing, enchantment and breeding
Added avatar items to the download context menu.

Potion brewing & potions
Enchanting
1.1 Feature: Bows are enchantable
Experience
1.3 Feature: Based on newer enchanting system. Maximum level for enchantment is 30 instead of 50
1.3 Feature: The player will receive experience from smelting and/or mining ores (e.g. iron ingots when smelting, redstone ores when mining).
1.4 Feature: Experience from breeding.
Animal breeding
1.4 Feature: Chickens are bred with seeds
End portal frame, brewing stand, enchantment table, cauldron, lily pad, nether bricks, nether brick fence, nether brick stairs, mycelium, end stone
Blaze rod, ghast tear, gold nugget, glass bottle, water bottle, spider eye, fermented spider eye, eye of ender, glistering melon, nether wart, blaze powder, bottle o' enchanting, magma cream

Blaze, snow golem, magma cubes, baby animals, mooshrooms, villagers
Mooshrooms can rarely spawn in plains biome
Villagers only appear as farmers and cannot trade, breed or open doors.

Skin-related animation for Skin Packs
Option to disable skin animation

Fences now attach to adjacent blocks.
Ender pearls can now be thrown to teleport in Survival and Creative mode (will take damage upon landing)
In creative mode, hostile mobs don't go after the player, unless attacked.
"Minecraft: Xbox 360 Edition Patch change logs" – Minecraft Forum, December 19, 2012.
